1. Schedule feed refresh -> GET <feed URL>
2. Parse feed JSON
    -> GET base content -> UNZIP base content (? -> MV files to content location)
    -> GET media content (? -> MV files to content location)
    -> MAP post data into post database
    ->



wp: scheme

wp:posts                                Return a list of all posts *1
wp:posts+type=page                      Return a list of pages
wp:posts+modifiedTime={time}            Return a list of posts modified at the specified time
wp:posts+modifiedTime.min={time}        Return a list of posts modified since the specified time
wp:posts+where={where clause}           ? General query form
wp:posts+filter={filter id}             ? Apply pre-defined filter
wp:posts/{id}                           Return post data *2
wp:posts/{id}+format={format}           ? Return post data in a specified format data/html

*1 Standard post list data return format suitable for configuring a list data source
   Note that the post's featured image is needed for list icons, auto-scaling of the image
   must be applied

*2 Standard post data return format suitable for configuring a webview, e.g.
{
    title:          {post title}
    content:        {post content}
    contentURL:     {file url to content directory path}
}
